reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great mount for 7 inch GPS
reviews.reviewText: First of all it appears well made and it matches my black interior. Secondly, it fits my Garmin drivesmart 65 7 inch screen. I used round velcro pads to attach it which were the perfect size - CHENGU 12 Pairs Referee Patch Hook and Loop Dots 3 Inch Self Sticky Circle Hook and Loop Round Adhesive Loop Tape Double Sided Hook and Loop Fasteners. I first cleaned the spot on the dash with 91% rubbing alcohol, let it dry, applied the pad to the dash and pressed for 2 mins. The next day, even in 58 degree weather it was stuck on extremely well. Then I pulled off the protective layer (just the big one, not the red one too) on the clamshell unit and stuck the other side of the velcro to it, holding, pressing for two minutes and I was good to go. It's really nice to use the velcro so you can plug in your GPS, put it in the holder and then put it on your dash. Plus you can readjust it any time you want. So far I love this thing, it's very well made and light but heavy enough to let you know it's good quality.

reviews.reviewText: Bought this for a snowmobile. The spring holding the clamshell together is not strong enough to keep the GPS in place. It needs a much stronger spring. The GPS would rattle out after a few minutes, and would have to be repositioned. Then, one decent size bump and my gps went flying and got run over by the guy behind me. Otherwise, the adhesion was good, but it simply isn't good for any kind of off road use.
Secure on dash, holds my 7” GPS tightly, does job well
